1 olive oil
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 tin sweetcorn
1 lemon
1 packet sour cream
1 bag slaw mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 packet Corn Chips
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Pickled Jalapeños
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook chicken, until browned and cooked through, 6-7 mins
• Add spice blend, garlic paste and a splash of water
• Cook until fragrant, 1-2 mins

• Meanwhile, drain corn. Cut lemon into wedges
• In a bowl, combine sour cream, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of oil
• Add corn, slaw and spinach. Season and toss

• Microwave rice until steaming,2-3 mins
• Plate up rice, slaw and chicken
• Top with jalapeños, crumbled cheese and aioli
• Crumble with corn chips to serve